(44, 3, 17, 46, 2, 8, 8, 'through ignorance ye did it', 'Ignorance of Crucifixion', 'This connection highlights the theme of ignorance surrounding the crucifixion. Both passages emphasize that the actions taken were done in ignorance by those involved.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 3, 17, 54, 1, 13, 13, 'through ignorance', 'Ignorance in Actions', 'This connection highlights the theme of acting out of ignorance in both passages. Acts 3:17 mentions ignorance in the actions of the people and their rulers, while 1 Timothy 1:13 reflects on personal actions done in ignorance and unbelief.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 3, 17, 43, 7, 26, 27, 'through ignorance ye did it', 'Ignorance of Rulers', 'This connection highlights the theme of ignorance among the rulers regarding Jesus'' identity. In Acts, the acknowledgment of ignorance is present, while in John, the rulers'' uncertainty about Christ''s true identity is emphasized.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 3, 17, 44, 26, 9, 9, 'through ignorance', 'Ignorance and Misguided Actions', 'This connection highlights the theme of ignorance in both passages. In Acts 3:17, the acknowledgment of acting ''through ignorance'' parallels the sentiment in Acts 26:9, where the speaker reflects on doing ''many things contrary'' to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
