(44, 3, 18, 44, 2, 23, 23, 'that Christ should suffer', 'Connection of Prophecy and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize God''s foreknowledge and plan regarding Christ''s suffering and crucifixion. Acts 3:18 speaks of the fulfillment of prophecies about Christ''s suffering, while Acts 2:23 highlights the predetermined nature of His crucifixion.', 'prophecy', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 3, 18, 44, 26, 22, 23, 'that Christ should suffer', 'Connection of Christ''s Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize that Christ should suffer, as foretold by the prophets. This connection highlights the fulfillment of prophecy regarding the suffering of Christ.', 'prophecy', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 3, 18, 23, 50, 6, 6, 'that Christ should suffer', 'Connection of Suffering in Prophecy', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering foretold by the prophets. Acts 3:18 refers to Christ''s suffering, which is exemplified in Isaiah 50:6, where the imagery of physical abuse and shame is presented.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
